text:
It took me a minute to draft this review, because I'm a little torn on how to rate it.

It started out great, as we were greeted very nicely, offered a delicious welcome drink and a welcome massage (which we did not take advantage of). We were also allowed to check in early (we also got a late check out when we left, which we really appreciated).

When we got to the villa we were initially impressed but quickly noticed the lack of cleanliness. The table tops were sticky, the shelfs not dusted, the bathtub was filthy and had a bunch of hair in it and all the shiny surfaces, glass doors and such, had a lot of handprints and smears on them. I understand the difficulty of cleaning an outdoor bathroom, but we've had outdoor bathrooms in other hotels and they didn't look like that. 
We also didn't have toilet paper, but it was quickly delivered when we asked for it.

Another thing: about 5 minutes after our arrival we went outside to check out the outdoor area and closed the terrace door to not let insects in the villa. When we closed the door, it locked itself shut from the inside and we couldn't get back in. If we hadn't had our phone out to call the front desk, we would have been sitting there for god knows how long, roasting in the sun.
To me, a door that looks from the inside, when you just pull it shut, is a major design flaw.

So, the first impression wasn't all that great, but over the next few days this impressionen really changed.

First oft all: we loved our villa! We had one of the low level villas overlooking the valley (we had villa no. 7) with a lot of privacy and beautiful nature right in our backyard. The design is clean and chic. The bed was huge and comfy. If I had to change something, I would add a wastebasket in the living room, but everything else was pretty much perfect. Including the pool, which kept us refreshed even on the hottest days.

Even though the hotel is located just a 15 min walk (or 5 min shuttle ride, which they offer for free) from town, we mostly had dinner at our villa, because room service was reasonably priced, offered a huge variety and the food was without exception FANTASTIC.
Your personalized breakfast is served in your villa, in the afternoon you sometimes get a delicious refreshment and at night we usually got a late night snack, which was a sweet local delicacy with a short explanation. We really appreciated these small guestures and loved the food everytime.

We also had our laundry done here, which worked fine.
The hotel offers massages and such, the free shuttle, bikes you can use and will help you with tour planning.
They also have wifi in the entire hotel area, but it's not the fastest.

We were extremely impressed with the entire staff. Everyone was incredibly friendly  and helpful. I really can't say anything negative about any of the staff we interacted with.

Overall we really had a great stay here. It wasn't perfect and I would recommend retraining housekeeping, but everything else from the location, the food to the staff was just great. You really get great value for your money, so I still decided to rate 5 stars.
title: Great food, fantastic staff

text:
We were fortunate enough to be able to stay at Origin on our most recent trip to Bali. 
Origin is a holiday makers dream, a small boutique property comprised of only a small amount of villas set down a quiet street in Ubud with picturesque views. The sunsets over the pool making for a beautiful photo in the afternoons. 

We stayed in a one bedroom villa with private pool, beautiful semi outdoor bathroom (the bathtub is an Instagram must not miss opportunity!). Our room was clean and airy, with a modern industrial architecture & hints of Balinese traditional quirky ness in the decor - making you feel quiet at home from the moment you walk in.
 
The amenities where everything you needed and nothing you did not. One particular thing I loved personally ( some people may not) was the management an property owners decision to do away with soaps and toothbrush packs ect. Opting for a more sustainable and environmental friendly option with refillable bottles. Just remember to pack your own tooth paste and tooth brush. 

While the villa is perfect and you could stay there all day if you wanted to - they offer in villa massages by trained professionals. We each received a one hour full body massage. Perfect relaxing afternoon for couples or the whole family. Ubud Centre is just a short drive with the complementary shuttle service operating at specific times. You have no excuse not to explore Ubud and it’s beautiful restaurants & boutique shopping. While there, you will mostly likely be approached by a local taxi for a tour. text:
I stayed at Origin for 3 nights with my partner. I was truly one of the most relaxing hotel stays I have experienced. From being picked up from the airport (our driver spoke excellent English and provided cold water which was much appreciated) to checking out, we received exceptional service. Nothing was too much effort for the staff we met. When we arrived at the hotel, the kitchen was closed however the staff went out of their way to make sure we did not go to bed hungry and pulled together a small feast for us!
 
I think the big selling point for this hotel is the privacy, very closely followed by the view. The hotel is set in the middle of rice fields and you can enjoy a swim in your private pool while looking out to unobstructed view. In the morning, breakfast is delivered to your room where you can enjoy it at your leisure on the outdoor terrace. The selection of food for breakfast blew me away, as did the quality. I recommend trying the porridge (flavours change daily) and the fruit which is topped with homemade chia seed pudding. They also source bread from lovely bakeries daily.
 
The rooms are incredibly spacious and have a large outdoor bathroom which is very in keeping with the Bali feel around you. High quality products are provided for your use as are robes, sarongs and beach bags. There are all nice added extras. The terraces are very generous in size and have a very unique hammock over the pool which was so lovely to relax in after a big breakfast! The hotel recommends some restaurants to try during your time in Ubud of which we tried two (bridges and Naughty Nori’s). These were excellent recommendation that we really enjoyed and probably wouldn’t have experienced without the help of Origin!
 
The hotel is located about a 10/15 minute walk from the main streets so I would recommend this hotel for people who want to be within walking distance to the main Ubud area but would still like some luxury, calm and privacy. It was lovely to be able to get away from the hustle and bustle at the end of the day and we really looked forward to getting back to our room!
 
I would love to stay at Origin again and recommend it to anyone who is looking for a really special place to stay during their time in Bali.

text: I went to Ubud for three nights with my husband, dad and a friend of ours. It was my dad's first time in Bali and he came all the way from Ireland so we wanted to make it a trip to remember. We couldn't have been happier with Origin Ubud. We had two villas that were side by side both with beautiful infinity pools that overlooked the forest. The view was very special and serene. The part I loved most about the villas was the fact they were close to the town yet were in a peaceful village location. I could not compliment the staff of the Villa enough. From the moment we got there to the moment we left, the team were super attentive. We got breakfast in our villas every morning- make sure to ask for the bread selection, they have different jam preserves every morning that were simply delicious. It was my husband's birthday when we were there. I told the staff of the villa the day we arrived and two days later they remembered and about six of the team hand delivered a chocolate cake for my husband and sang him "Happy Birthday" it was so thoughtful, a really lovely personal touch. After a day of touring around Ubud we loved to come back to the villa late afternoon, have a few beers by the pool and order a light bite before we went out that evening. There is a gorgeous hammock over the pool with lots of cushions so it was very comfortable to lie there recounting our adventures from that day. Another touch that I loved was the welcome massage for everyone which was a 15min complimentary massage in the comfort of your own villa. The villa has a spa too so you can extend this massage if you wish to. Origin Ubud is a beautiful villa with a modern yet local feel, the staff do everything to cater for your needs - you can even settle your bill when checking out in your own villa. We will be back again for sure- can't wait!
title: Beautiful Villa close to centre of Ubud

text:
If you’re with little kids, this is a perfect place for your vacation. Everything was designed to be safe for kids, including where they put the electrical sockets. They set up a tent full of toys too, even tho most of them are not working. Our kids loved this place!

They also have an impressive service; they bring your food in if you order online, and deliver coffee to your room. We also left some things after check out and they kept them for us.

However, the smell of smoke from mosquito repellent they put inside the room everyday, was bothering us. We also had problem with wooden patio in the back porch, which was broken and almost hurt my husband - since then we’re very concern to let the kids out to the tent or pool.

We recommend you to have your own vehicle if you want to stay in this villa. It’s somehow walking distance from the center, but not if you’re with the kids, and they don’t provide free shuttle. Having your own vehicle also help you to go around for breakfast or dinner, since they also don’t provide a restaurant and breakfast for guests. Basically, it’s a nice place to stay, but you need to do most of the things by yourself.

text:
Where to start? There is so much that is lovely about this place but for our visit the negatives far outweighed the positives. 
The most disappointing aspect was the fact that there is a multistorey hotel being built opposite the resort looking directly into the so-called private pool, garden and room. 
Construction starts at 7am and goes through until at least 6pm every day, no exceptions. 
NO PRIVACY at all and continuous noise. 

We would see the workmen and they could see us. 
I’ve no idea what the resort is planning to do about this in the future but any pending guests be warned. 
As for the rest…
Positives
1.       The staff are uniformly lovely and keen to provide optimal service…there’s just a bit of a mismatch about what this means when the resort promotes itself as a luxurious retreat…
2.       The bed is comfortable and spacious
3.       The bathroom is equally spacious and well-kitted out with standard amenities (shower, bath gel, conditioner) all in large side pump packs. However, there are no other amenities such as ear buds, razor etc.
4.       Each room has two golf umbrellas at door as well as a supply at main entrance – much needed during the off-season when we were staying.
5.       The reservations team do pay attention to notes re if a special occasion – this was part of our wedding anniversary holiday so first night we were presented with a plate with a cake and inscription in chocolate wishing us happy anniversary.
6.       Gym access is provided at Ubud Fitness centre which is an easy stroll away, down the road and in a side street. [The fact we had to ask for this instead of it automatically being provided contributed to the series of not-quite-right, ‘small omissions’ that contributed to an overall dissatisfaction but still brilliant that provided.]
7.       Welcome drinks described as an inclusion on arrival and were much needed due to issues with locating the resort (will describe further below) however we ended up having to ask for same once in room. They may well have turned up without asking but for other resorts, a welcome drink is what you’re handed when you sit down to fill out the check-in paperwork and photocopying of passport…
8.       Package included a 15-minute complementary massage each. Again, had to ask. Didn’t happen 1st day. Asked again 2nd day & was confirmed for between 11am and 1pm. Didn’t happen. 3rd day, received a WhatsApp message saying staff would be onsite and what time would we like. Booked and confirmed. Girls arrived promptly but turns out the massage is a foot massage only – not the next and shoulders we were hoping to be able to have. The therapists were very good and provided a 30 min foot/calf massage each with the resort offering to extend it to an hour to apologise for our room not being made up earlier that day but we declined. When the massage is only for the lower limb, half an hour is more than adequate but a gracious gesture nonetheless.
9.       There was no coffee provided in room – we only hoped for instant as in any other place – but once queried the team went out & bought back 3 different types of instant coffee. Well & truly above & beyond (unfortunately all varieties included sugar in their mix but really touched that they tried)
10.   The complimentary shuttle service was terrific and they didn’t stick to their very odd timetable (see attached). However, we only needed to use the first evening (pouring rain) because once orientated to our area, we could walk to the centre of town in less time than it took the shuttle as Ubud is a town riddled with one-way streets and massive traffic congestion even now during off-season. If you do use the shuttle, don’t expect fancy – we were informed it was a new bus but still only has a bench seat (padded) each side, no aircon and sliding windows left open but fabulous driver and very responsive service to pick up (there is just the one drop-off and pickup point)
11.   Location, location, location. Once we became accustomed to navigating the very busy narrow road, we were within walking distance to everything that Ubud had to offer.
Negatives
1.       Very difficult to locate, even for our local driver and using navigation. The map would say we had arrived but could not find any signage. This situation was compounded by the fact the road is two-way but not even single lane width with no verges and very limited opportunities to pullover or drive slowly. When I say ‘busy’ I mean the road was literally swarming with mopeds, motorbikes, cyclists, cars, foot traffic. It took four, FOUR drive pasts and two phone calls from our driver to the resort - and then staff coming out and waiting for us before entry was located. It’s not like we could just turn around when missed – as the marker on the navigation imprecise, by the time it had moved to show we had passed resort, there was nowhere to even vaguely turn around so each ‘miss’ meant driving a few further km before being able to turn around and try again. A situation that would readily be fixed by hanging a shingle out and changing the giant Origin sign on the side of the building from the current black metalwork (on dark grey background) to something that stands out. The irony is that once found it is really easy to describe location by simply saying once on the street, when you reach the 1st road to the right, immediately pull into the 1st indent on the left literally adjacent to that street & the giant temple on the corner!
2.       Whilst the staff are keen, it became very hit & miss what was remembered and what wasn’t. in terms of recalling guest preferences (bear in in mind only 4 villas occupied during our stay). It became exhausting having to request things that anywhere else would either happen automatically or be remembered. Being willing doesn’t counteract the act of constantly having to ask – our request for milk WAS remembered & was supplied daily without any further request but other things not so great...
Examples: A, full complement of towels face washers etc. on check in. Next day, face towels removed and not replaced. Rang housekeeping & supplied. Same again following but we just gave up & used the hand towels as a substitute.
B. Shower cap used and not replaced. Had to ask,2nd & when still not replaced 3rd day, gave up asking.
C. No ice available in room nor self-service access so 1st rang and requested. After ten minutes went and asked up at the backroom near reception and provided. This detail not recalled so each day thereafter at around the same time, I had to call and request delivery.
D. I used the notepad up and requested replacement. Promptly provided but when I went to use it was actually devoid of paper so had to request again.
E. The compendium details to use the ‘do not disturb’ sign if not wanting to be disturbed. We did this once and restored to usual. However, we went out 2nd day for 4 hours during which time we had a WhatsApp communication with the team where we mentioned we were in town. Returned to room exhausted at 2pm to discover it had not been made up and breakfast dishes still sitting there. Rang to request and was told that they didn’t know we were out. I explained re the WhatsApp communication and more to the point why hadn’t housekeeping even attempted when there was no do not disturb sign? This was unable to be answered. Housekeeping team did come and do our room but later we discovered absence of face towel and teaspoons not replaced.
This is not an exhaustive list but just examples of a series of minor issues that collectively meant staying here was not relaxing - especially when you add in the unrelenting construction noise.
3.       Despite the compendium asking guests to leave their room key at reception when they go out for any reason, there is NO reception! Nor a phone there to use if needing to make contact. Needless to say, we didn’t abide by this request. However, even had there been a phone supplied in this lounge/entry area, we found on two occasions (still daylight hours) when we rang “reception” (dial 0) no one answered necessitating me walking up and poking my head into the only open door to seek assistance.
4.       In-room slides are supplied (too short for his feet and too wide for both our feet) but no bathrobes. Two lengths of fabric are supplied on hangers in the wardrobe which could have been beach towels or very heavy sarongs but that’s it. Most odd when even lower-end hotels seem to supply bathrobes.
5.       Finally – and this ended up becoming the most disappointing – things left behind apparently are chucked out! We only left one item in the bathroom – but it was an expensive, travel ‘wash bag’ which is able to be used to wash clothes swiftly & efficiently yet is able to be compressed very small for packing. I had rinsed it out and left to dry behind the sink taps in bathroom but as was also white/cream like the wall it was resting against, both my husband & I missed it. Unfortunately, we then did not notice until went to use it at our next destination. In response to my email query re same, all I got was a statement staying the team would keep an eye out! Erm, no. we should have been alerted as soon as room cleaned that we had left this item behind.
title: Unrelenting construction noise & lack of privacy negates all positives

My wife and I just got back from a 9 night stay at Origin Ubud (6 nights initially, and then came back for 3 more since we loved it so much!). We loved the design, location and service that we received at this boutique hotel. The small number of villas meant it was a quiet and relaxing stay. The rooms were clean, large with a minimalist design that we both appreciated. A-la cart breakfast was awesome and delivered to you room daily at your selected time. Having a pool in the room allowed for quiet relaxing dips to cool off from the heat. The service we received was amazing, they treated us like family - big shout out to Koko and Widi who made our stay extra special - they booked trips/transportation/scooter rentals for us. Even brought us some herbal tea when one of us wasn't feeling the greatest one night. Located on a quieter street just outside of Ubud Center - the shuttle made for efficient trips to town (or a short walk down the street leads you to the main road as well). Having a scooter would allow you to do more exploring at your own pace as well.

Highly recommended! Origin Ubud would be our top choice next time we come back to Bali!

text:
The Origin Ubud was probably beautiful when it was first built, but the hotel itself is a little worn and could use some love. It is in a quiet location and you are really surrounded by jungle. The rooms are spacious and attractive, but we found that there were a trail of ants around the door at all times. There were many dead squished bugs in the window curtains, and the white towels were worn and stained. The pool also had quite a bit of leaves in it. Not a huge deal- this is a rural area after all but these are reasons that this is a four star rating for me rather than five. While it is within walking distance to main attractions, it isn’t an enjoyable walk as there are few sidewalks and it is on a narrow road. However, the hotel provides a shuttle into town and also can quickly arrange transport. 

The hotel can arrange many activities for you and they deliver a beautiful breakfast spread each morning. You can also order room service and drinks (decent), and there is a stocked mini fridge. 

Overall, we found the hotel itself to be underwhelming compared to the pictures but the customer service was amazing. They were exceedingly friendly and were able to arrange everything we needed from airport transfers to rides to dinner. They even packed us breakfast when we had to leave early. Widi especially stands out for his fantastic service. I would recommend this hotel for families or people who want a nice quality hotel but are on a budget.

text:
If you’re reading this review because you’re considering booking a stay at The Origin Ubud - don’t have any doubts, you definitely should book to stay here it is beyond amazing. 

The private pool villas are absolutely gorgeous and the staff treated us like royalty. The “lobby” is also a lovely place to relax and everything is very simplistic, and modern. Wifi is easy to access and over a four night stay only didn’t work for 10 minutes. Pretty good! 

We were in Villa number 6 which was at the bottom and had a great unobstructed view of nature. We watched coconuts being cut from the tree opposite every morning with breakfast - amazing! 

Location in Ubud is good, walking distance from the town centre and you can also hire scooters from reception which I recommend doing! Only 75,000 IDR per day. You can get a SIM card from down the road to help you navigate. They also have a free shuttle that runs to and from Ubud Centre throughout the day (a cute little blue van!) 

When we arrived we were given welcome drinks, shown around and had a lovely complimentary in room massage. All of the dining is done in your villa, breakfast delivered at your requested time each morning (they have lots of options and encourage you to get a few - even vegan friendly although twice there must’ve been a mistake they delivered mine with egg on the side which I just took off.)! You can also choose to have a floating breakfast in your private pool which is very luxurious. It seemed like we were the only people in the villas at the time of staying - thats how private it feels. Every night someone comes to turn down your bed, and fill up the mosquito oil burners (which meant we had ZERO bug problems! ) as well as deliver a “midnight snack” with a different traditional treat and story each night. 

Staff always greeted us with a smile and tried their best to help out however they could. It seemed everyone knew our names and genuinely wanted to make sure we had the best stay possible. The only thing lacking was perhaps a little knowledge / information on the area from some staff that you may receive at a large resort - but the manager (a lovely lady forgot her name sadly :() was very knowledgeable and assisted us with everywhere we wanted to go. 

We wanted to book a car to take us to our next hotel in Uluwatu and a staff member assisted us to find the cheapest safe option (400,000)- rather than the 60 USD charged at the hotel normally. 

The General Manager even came to see us off  - asked about our stay and was very friendly. What service!

Abbiamo un'unica rimostranza relativa alle escursioni: l'hotel propone alcune "esperienze" fuori dagli itinerari turistici che si sono rivelate, a nostro personale avviso, gitarelle un po' improvvisate a prezzi assurdamente alti per ciò che viene in concreto offerto. In particolare, durante un'escursione a piedi nella giungla, le cose non sono andate esattamente come dovuto: la "guida" ha seriamente rischiato di perdersi costringendoci a passare da un itinerario piuttosto pericoloso. Quando pochi giorni dopo abbiamo fatto check out ci siamo rese conto che ci era stato addebitato un costo per l'escursione inferiore a quello pattuito. Abbiamo creduto si trattasse di un gesto di cortesia considerato l'inconveniente che avevamo avuto, ma una volta tornate in Italia ci hanno scritto via what's up dicendo che si era trattato di un errore e che avrebbero proceduto ad addebitarci la differenza d'importo direttamente sui dati della carta di credito con cui avevamo effettuato la prenotazione, cosa che hanno in effetti fatto nonostante mi sia permessa di far notare che mi pareva un gesto scortese e poco professionale.
In sintesi: soggiornate all'Origin Ubud, ma evitate di fare escursioni con loro!
title: Tutto al top, ma...

Siamo state in queste piccole villette per il nostro soggiorno a Ubud e ne siamo rimaste innamorate! Isolate da qualsiasi rumore cittadino e lontane dalle altre villette, ogni appartamento è studiato affinchè ci si possa sentire immersi nella giungla.
Ogni giorno ti portano uno stuzzichino cucinato da loro e ogni giorno è possibile scegliere tra varie opzioni e gustare la colazione in camera....davvero squisita e abbondante!
Le camere sono ampie e spaziose: dotate di ogni comfort. Letti ampi, vasca da bagno immersa nel verde e piscina privata, con tanto di amaca sospesa sulla superficie, che si affaccia sulla giungla.
Un ambiente davvero rilassante e intimo!
Personale molto accogliente e gentile.
Unica nota che non ho apprezzato è da riferirsi alla navetta dell'hotel. Una sera abbiamo chiesto di essere portate (a pagamento) ad un ristorante specificando che saremmo poi ritornate da sole (avevamo pianificato altro). Il signore che ha organizzato il trasporto ha chiesto alla cameriera del ristorante di avvisarlo quando avremmo terminato di mangiare così da riaccompagnarci in hotel, senza minimamente avvisarci e facendoci pagare la corsa non richiesta! Abbiamo pagato per un servizio non richiesto e questa nota, francamente, mi ha un poco delusa...non me lo aspettavo...consiglio, pertanto, un po' più di accortezza perché un episodio simile potrebbe influire sulla piacevolezza del soggiorno ed è davvero un peccato perché la strutture merita!
Se mai dovessi tornare a Ubud, tornerò sicuramente all'Origin.
title: Spettacolare! Immersi nella giungla!

ウブド市街地は想像以上に騒がしく、
大通りを歩いていると観光客の多さに若干疲弊してしまうが、
そんな街中から少し離れた場所にあるのがこのホテル。

到着してまず迎えてくれるのは、
とても気さくで笑顔の絶えない現地のスタッフ達。
それまでに10日間ほどバリ中を放浪し
たまたま体調を崩していた自分に対して、
ハーブの入ったジンジャーティーをサービスで出してくれた。（お陰で体調はすぐに回復）
そしてなんといっても外と繋がっているモダンなロビー。
個人的にとても好きな空間で、
ウェルカムドリンクを飲みながら長旅の疲れを風に当たりながら癒やす。

部屋に案内されると、
一面の窓の先には新緑に映える真っ青なプール。
本当に暑い日だったので、
すぐにTシャツを脱ぎ捨てて飛び込んだ。
澄んだ水にタイル貼りのプールは本当にきれい。
部屋も落ち着いた雰囲気にビシッと張られたシーツ、
掃除の行き届いた水回りに満足。

おなかも空いていたのでバリ料理のお昼を頼んだところ、
その美味しさにびっくり。
しっかりとした現地の味付けなのだが、
日本人の好みにも合うようなアレンジが絶妙。
値段も高くなく、
町中の観光客向けのバリ料理レストランに行く気がなくなってしまった。

次の日からはホテルでバイクを借りて、
山の方を嫁と二人で探検したり
街中で買い物をしたりしてのんびり過ごす。
なんといってもホテルから街と反対方向に
しばらく走った所にある小さな町々は、
どこか日本の田園風景を想起させるような素敵な景色。
観光客のほとんどいないそう言った場所に
手軽にいけるのもこのホテルの良さだろう。

そんなこんなで快適に三泊を過ごし、
最後の晩ご飯は嫁に秘密でromantic dinnerというものを頼んでおいた。（一応新婚旅行だったので）
どんな事になるのかと少しどきどきしながら部屋に戻ると、、
ここから先は是非実際に行って確かめて欲しい。

空港までの送迎タクシーも手配してくれるので、
何の気兼ねなくウブドが楽しめるはず。
ぜひウブド旅行を検討している人は訪れてみては。
title: 喧騒から離れ、心遣いの行き届いたモダンなホテルへ。

Sejour en Novembre 2017 pour la 2nd fois a Bali et Ubud, apres 10 jours a Seminiak et 10 a Lombok. Parfait. De l'accueil au depart, rien a dire, si ce n'est parfait.
Le petit dejeuner est servis chasue matin dans la chambre, sur la terrasse avec piscine. Il faut la veille indiquer a la reception ce que l'on desir. Tres copieux et complet, il y en a pour tous les gouts.
Personnel tres accueillant, chaleureux et serviable, toujours de bon conseil pour visiter Ubud. Demande de lit bébé fourni le lendemain car manque de materiel. Nous avons demandé, couettes et oreillers supplementaires pour faire un "lit" a notre fils, le temps d'avoir le vrai lit, le personnel s'en est chargé en faisant un petit lit tout mignon. Parfait !!
Menage fait parfaitement, apres notre sortie de la chambre (a souligner), chaque soir on vient vous apportez des petites douceurs locales et meme temps que l'on prepare la chambre pour la nuit !!!

Chambre design, tres spacieuse, epurée, tout a fait au gout du jour. Grande terrasse avec herbe, table et chaise. Une sorte de hamac incrustée a la piscine fait office de transat. Vu sur la jungle. Superbe !!

Magnifique salle de bain. Baignoire a decouvert, avec de vraies plantes en deco. Douche tres pratique. Eau tres chaude et puissance de jet !!!!

Bref, y aller les yeux fermés !!!

Heerlijke prive verblijven. Zon staat precies op het goede moment op de tuin waardoor je de hele dag aan het prive zwembad zou kunnen liggen. Lekkere "hangmat" bover het zwembad met kussens.
Mooie kamer, modern en nieuw. Prachtige badkamer. Je hebt er een fijn gevoel van vrijheid je hoeft geen andere gasten te zien. 

Personeel was heel vriendelijk. Ze hebben een privetaxi voor ons geregeld (aanrader een local die je mooie plekken kan laten zie ) en een restaurant reservering en een tour. Heel hoog level van gastvrijheid. Je wordt echt in de watten gelegd. 

Ligging is lekker rustig. Wel een eindje van het centrum. 15 minuutjes lopen. (Terug een beetje bergopwaarts) maar er is ook een shuttle die heel fijn is. 

Was heerlijk om even bij te komen!

text: Встретили очень доброжелательно, был массаж по заселению 10 мин, вэлкам дринк. Дизайн номеров потрясающий, личный бассейн тоже впечатляет. Завтрак вкусный, хоть принесли не с первого раза все, что мы заказывали вечером. О минусах. Как только заселились, положили личные вещи на стол, я подошла взять телефон, на столе были липкие пятна из под стаканов, не знаю сок или газировка, в общем много кругов. Стол для завтрака во дворике был также грязный, перед завтраком я сама его протирала, полотенце стало чёрным, но я хоть убедилась что мне не кажется и что стол не старый/просто потертый...Он действительно был грязным и его достаточно легко было бы протереть персоналу. Тапочки только одни, пришлось просить и ждать, при том что писали несколько раз, что нас двое, мы молодожены и тд. Стены и двери в туалете тоже забрызганы чем-то желтым, боюсь представить чем именно)) Место с необыкновенно классным дизайном, но видимо из-за большого спроса, персонал решил подзабить на элементарные вещи, из которых и складывается общее впечатление!
